# Cloudflare Pages headers (#218). Copied into the Pages publish dir (dist/).
#
# IMPORTANT: do NOT long-cache JSON/manifest/SW. A transient bad response (e.g.
# an index.html fallback served for an asset URL during an outage) must never get
# stuck in players' browser HTTP cache. The real game assets are served from
# jsDelivr via _redirects and cached there as immutable, so these rules only
# affect the few files Pages serves directly (locales, manifest, the SW) — for
# those, "no-cache" = always revalidate (cheap 304s), never serve stale.

# The HTML entry point MUST always revalidate: it references the content-hashed JS
# bundle (assets/index-<hash>.js), so a stale cached index.html keeps players on the
# OLD code even after a fresh deploy (e.g. they couldn't see the Ace/Elite/Hell run
# changes). With no-cache the browser revalidates every load (cheap 304), and the
# new index.html points at the new bundle hashes -> fresh code. No save impact
# (saves live in localStorage, which the HTTP cache never touches).
/
  Cache-Control: no-cache

/index.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache

/*.json
  Cache-Control: no-cache

/manifest.webmanifest
  Cache-Control: no-cache

/service-worker.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache
